{"atom_id":"md_dmRELREC_ex_a040","file":"knowledge_base/domains/RELREC/examples.md","line_start":66,"line_end":66,"parent_section":"§RELREC.2.1 [Example 1]","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"In the sponsor's operational database, these datasets may have existed as either separate datasets that were merged for analysis, or a single dataset that may have included observations from more than 1 general observation class (e.g., Events and Findings). The value in IDVAR must be the name of the key used to merge/join the 2 datasets. In this example, the --LNKID variable is used as the key to identify the related observations. The values for the --LNKID variable in the 2 datasets are sponsor-defined. Although other variables may also serve as a single merge key when the corresponding values for IDVAR are equal, --GRPID, --SPID, --REFID, --LNKID, or --LNKGRP are typically used for this purpose.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"general-purpose","prompt_version":"P0_writer_md_v1.9.2","ts":"2026-05-07T00:00:00Z"}}
